results.description:
Join us as we discuss: how to avoid the pitfalls of writing CSS; how browsers understand the CSS stack; how to work WITH CSS selector specificity and not against it; the Inverted Triangle CSS Methodology; and touch on Sass project management. BEGINNERS WELCOME! 

This talk will be given by The Jared Wilcurt. He's the creator of Scout-App 2 (scout-app.io), a cross-platform desktop application that processes Sass files into CSS; and works as a UI Engineer for Salesforce.

Everyone is welcome regardless of industry or skill level!

results.name: How to be Successful at Freelancing

results.description:
How fast does your website load? If you are responsible for publishing and maintaining content for your organization’s website the answer to this question greatly depends on your strategy for web performance. Good web performance is a key trait in attracting new and returning visitors, and it’s also a factor in how search engines index websites for search. In this introductory class on web performance you will learn why web performance matters, how to use free tools to gain insights into the size and performance of your website, and learn about some simple and effective techniques for optimizing your content for blazing speeds. This class is introductory and accessible to all skill levels!

Food will be provided by Ion Three from 6pm. Talk will begin at 6:30.
results.name: Website Optimization

* Why and how should you use it? 

** Please bring your laptop.

results.name: Intro to Git/Github
